# tools/check-no-direct-llm-fetch.allowlist
#
# cycle-103 sprint-1 T1.7 — exempt-file list for the drift gate. Each entry
# is a path (rooted at PROJECT_ROOT) that is allowed to reference provider
# API URLs directly. Adding entries here is a PR-visible governance act —
# include a rationale comment next to each line.
#
# Format:
#   - One path per line.
#   - Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#   - Path-match is EXACT (no globs, no recursion).
#
# To migrate an exempt entry out of this file, the entry's call sites must
# route through .claude/adapters/cheval.py (via call_flatline_chat for
# bash, ChevalDelegateAdapter for TS, or direct cheval invocation for
# Python). Then delete the entry from this file.
#
# =============================================================================

# Operator-visible direct curl (health probes). The /v1/models / /v1/messages
# endpoints are hit at probe time to verify provider reachability — different
# semantics from app-level fetches. Migrating to cheval would require
# round-tripping probe data through model-invoke, which adds latency without
# behavioral gain. Migration tracked as out-of-scope.
.claude/scripts/model-health-probe.sh

# Legacy adapter shim — already marked `.legacy` extension. Scheduled for
# sunset in a follow-up cycle (cycle-099 sprint-4 legacy-sunset path).
# Direct provider URLs here are vestigial.
.claude/scripts/model-adapter.sh.legacy

# Embeddings call (cycle-103 T1.6 audit doc — handoffs/T1.6-flatline-api-audit.md
# §"embeddings exception"). Cheval has no embeddings substrate;
# `CompletionRequest` models chat completion only. Migration deferred until
# `loa_cheval.providers.base` grows an `embed()` method. Tracked for cycle-104+.
.claude/scripts/flatline-semantic-similarity.sh

# Legacy gpt-review-api routing fallback (`call_api()` function). When
# `hounfour.flatline_routing: false`, gpt-review-api.sh and related
# subsystems fall through this path. Migrating requires routing
# gpt-review-api through `model-invoke` unconditionally — out of cycle-103
# scope (cycle-099 sprint-1B already migrated other adapters; this is the
# remaining fallback). Note: `call_api_via_model_invoke()` and the new
# `call_flatline_chat()` in this same file ARE the unified path; only the
# legacy `call_api()` keeps direct curls.
.claude/scripts/lib-curl-fallback.sh

# Library-internal provider-host references (NOT fetches).
# endpoint-validator.py: docstrings + defensive code that mention the URLs.
# model-probe-cache.py: provider→(host, port) map used by socket-level
# probes — not HTTP, just TCP handshake verification.
.claude/scripts/lib/endpoint-validator.py
.claude/scripts/lib/model-probe-cache.py

# cycle-108 sprint-2 T2.L (cheval-network-guard.sh). The file's allowlist
# constant `_LOA_NETWORK_GUARD_ALLOWLIST` enumerates LLM provider hosts
# (api.anthropic.com, api.openai.com, generativelanguage.googleapis.com,
# etc.) as strings — they are not API calls, they are the allowlist that
# blocks non-allowlisted hosts when LOA_NETWORK_RESTRICTED=1. Same
# disposition as endpoint-validator.py's docstring URLs.
.claude/scripts/lib/cheval-network-guard.sh
